Karan   Mehandru  General Partner , Trinity VenturesAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 10 Board Members in 10 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships----
Background

		Mr. Karan Mehandru serves as a General Partner at Trinity Ventures and Trinity Ventures XI, L.P. Mr. Mehandru joined Trinity Ventures as a Principal in 2010 and focuses on infrastructure, next generation datacenter infrastructure technologies, systems, big datacloud, cloud computing, enterprise software, mobile and SaaS. He has more than ten years of experience in product development, sales and marketing, enterprise software and systems, Big Data, SaaS, semiconductors, ... consumer electronics and next generation datacenter infrastructure technologies. He served as a Principal at Trinity Ventures and was a part of its enterprise team. Prior to this, he served as a Senior Associate at Scale Venture Partners. At Scale, he focused on identifying investment opportunities in enterprise software and systems, semiconductors, consumer electronics and next generation datacenter infrastructure technologies including storage, virtualization and cloud computing, enterprise software and SaaS. He served as a Strategic Sales Account Manager at Synopsys Inc. At Synopsys, he was instrumental in closing more than $40 million in strategic and territorial design wins from 2006 to 2007 and directed the sales effort for its software suite, IP and professional services. He also led marketing, applications and sales efforts for his team's top accounts and worked closely with Synopsys' strategic customers and the product management team on the development of new products. He served as a Senior Applications Consultant for implementation product line at Synopsys. Prior to Synopsys, he served as an Implementation Manager at PMC-Sierra, Ltd. with a focus on the fabless semiconductor market. During his five years with PMC-Sierra, he led and managed design implementation of large scale ASICs targeted for the telecommunications, enterprise storage and networking markets. He successfully led PMC-Sierra's design implementation team through their first customer ASIC project with Cisco Systems. He spent ten years as an operator in various roles in product management, marketing and sales. He takes a thematic approach to investing and focus on B2B companies that are capitalizing on secular trends like consumerization of the enterprise, Software as a Service, Big Data and mobile. He has different roles ranging from Chief Executive Officer counsel to the “SaaS metrics expert. In most cases he aims to be a resource for the Chief Executive Officer and other executive team members in hiring, product strategy, financing, marketing and sales. He has been a Director of Simply Measured, Inc. since March 2014, Boomerang Commerce, Inc. since July 16, 2014 and Mobile Data Labs, Inc. since January 30, 2015. He serves as a Director of Act-On Software, Inc. and RJMetrics Inc. He has been a Director at Auth0, Inc. since August 24, 2016. He serves as a Director at Outreach since June 22, 2016. He serves as a Director of Jama Software, Inc. since August 19, 2013. He served as a Board Observer of Jama Software, Inc. He served as a Director at Preact, Inc. since April 18, 2014. Mr. Mehandru holds an M.S. in Management Science and Engineering from Stanford University with a specialization in Technology and Entrepreneurship. He graduated from Carleton University in Ottawa, Canada with an Honors B.S. in Electrical Engineering with high distinction.Read Full Background




